    <a href="/reviews/" class="hero-pill">
      <span class="pill-dot"></span>
      <span>Tool review · hands-on testing</span>
      <span class="pill-arrow">→</span>
    </a>
    <h1 class="h-display"><span class="accent">Serpstat Review</span> (2026): Best Budget SEO Suite?</h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">We tested Serpstat's keyword research, competitor analysis, site audits, and rank tracking. It's genuinely impressive for the price — especially the Tree View and AI clustering. Here's what it does well, where it falls short, and who should pick something else.</p>
    <div class="hero-ctas">
      <a href="/checkout/" class="btn btn-primary"><span>Try theStacc instead — $1 trial <span class="arrow">→</span></span></a>
      <a href="#verdict" class="btn btn-secondary">Jump to the verdict</a>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span><strong>4.2★</strong> from <strong>464</strong> verified reviews (G2: 4.6, Capterra: 4.5)</span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>From <strong>$69/mo</strong></span>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta-item">
        <span>Last updated <strong>Q2 2026</strong></span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- AT-A-GLANCE VERDICT -->
  <section class="modules-bento" id="verdict">
    <div class="modules-tabs-header">
      <span class="label-pill">At a glance</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Serpstat, <span class="accent">in 30 seconds.</span></h2>
      <p class="lede">Best value in keyword research and competitor analysis. No content creation, no local SEO — research stops where the work begins.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bento-grid">
      <div class="bento-card bento-feature">
        <div class="bento-num">★</div>
        <div class="bento-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polygon points="12 2 15.09 8.26 22 9.27 17 14.14 18.18 21.02 12 17.77 5.82 21.02 7 14.14 2 9.27 8.91 8.26 12 2"/></svg>
        </div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Our verdict: 4.2 / 5</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">The <span class="accent">best-value keyword research and competitor analysis tool</span> — and research-only.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Serpstat delivers keyword research, competitor analysis, site auditing, and rank tracking at half the price of Semrush. The Tree View visualization and AI semantic clustering are genuinely standout features. What it doesn't do: create content, manage local SEO, or publish anything. You still need writers.</p>
        <ul class="bento-list">
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Best for: freelance SEOs, small agencies, affiliate marketers</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Price: from $69/mo · 7-day free trial, no card</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Strength: Tree View, AI clustering, support 9.4/10</li>
          <li><svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="3"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>Weakness: no content creation, no local SEO</li>
        </ul>
        <div class="bento-mock">
          <div class="bento-mock-bar">
            <div class="bento-mock-meta">SERPSTAT · 4.2/5 · KEYWORD RESEARCH + COMPETITOR ANALYSIS</div>
            <span class="bento-mock-pulse"></span>
          </div>
          <div class="bento-mock-title">Best for: freelancers and small agencies on a budget</div>
          <div class="bento-mock-tags">
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">$69/mo</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag">Tree View</span>
            <span class="bento-mock-tag brand">Research only</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bento-cta">Need content written? Try theStacc instead <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card">
        <div class="bento-num">✓</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Pick Serpstat if</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">You want <span class="accent">keyword research and competitor analysis</span> at half the Semrush price.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">Freelance SEO, solo practitioner, small agency, affiliate marketer researching product-review keywords. Intuitive, beginner-friendly, excellent support, great Tree View visualization.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">serpstat.com <span class="arrow">→</span></div>
      </div>

      <div class="bento-card">
        <div class="bento-num">✗</div>
        <h3 class="bento-title">Skip Serpstat if</h3>
        <h4 class="bento-sub">You need <span class="accent">content created, local SEO managed,</span> or backlinks researched deeply.</h4>
        <p class="bento-desc">No content writing, no GBP management, and a backlink index that's noticeably thinner than Ahrefs. Local businesses and link builders need different tools.</p>
        <div class="bento-cta">See why theStacc fits better <span class="arrow">↓</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS SERPSTAT -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">What is Serpstat</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">An <span class="accent">all-in-one SEO platform</span> from Odesa, Ukraine.</h2>
      <p>Serpstat is an all-in-one SEO platform founded in 2013 in Odesa, Ukraine as an internal tool at Netpeak digital marketing agency. Launched as standalone SaaS in 2015, it analyzes search engine data through keyword research, competitor analysis, site auditing, backlink checking, and rank tracking. The name combines SERP (Search Engine Results Page) and statistics. The platform serves primarily Eastern European, CIS, and North American markets with a keyword database covering billions of terms across 230+ regional Google databases.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">What makes Serpstat worth serious consideration is the price-to-feature ratio and the quality of its keyword research tools. The Tree View visualization shows hierarchical keyword relationships that most tools present as flat lists — genuinely useful for content planning. The AI semantic clustering groups related terms automatically, cutting manual spreadsheet work significantly.</p>
        <p style="color: var(--text-2); margin: 0 0 16px;">The ceiling is clear. Serpstat's backlink index is smaller than Ahrefs and Semrush. Traffic estimation accuracy ranks lowest in independent tests (18.9%). Site audits produce false positives that require manual verification. And there's no content creation, no local SEO toolkit, no GBP management. It's a research tool — what you do with the research is entirely up to you.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PROS / CONS -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The honest pros & cons</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Serpstat gets right — <span class="accent">and where it lets you down.</span></h2>
      <p>After hands-on testing across keyword research, competitor analysis, and site auditing, here's the unvarnished list.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Pros</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Serpstat shines</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five genuine strengths worth your attention.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Exceptional value for the price</h4>
              <p>Best value for money among all-in-one SEO suites at this tier. $69/month vs $129–$139 for Ahrefs/Semrush — delivers keyword research, competitor analysis, rank tracking, and site auditing at roughly half the cost.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Outstanding keyword research tools</h4>
              <p>The Tree View visualization shows hierarchical keyword relationships no competitor presents as clearly. AI-powered semantic clustering groups related terms automatically. Together they cut manual content planning time significantly.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Superior customer support</h4>
              <p>Customer support scores 9.4/10 on G2 — the highest in the category. Consistently praised across review platforms. When you're stuck on something urgent, this matters more than any feature list.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Intuitive interface with fast onboarding</h4>
              <p>Clean interface with a learning curve most new users clear in under an hour. Compared to Semrush's complexity, Serpstat feels approachable. New users find actionable keywords in their first session.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Generous trial and API access on all plans</h4>
              <p>7-day free trial without a credit card — one of the most generous evaluation windows in the category. API access available on all paid plans, unlike Semrush which restricts it to higher tiers.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ba-col before">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Cons</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">Where Serpstat falls short</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Five honest weaknesses we can't ignore.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Zero content creation capabilities</h4>
              <p>Purely a research tool. No AI writing, no content editor, no publishing. You find the keywords — then you're on your own to write, optimize, and publish everything the data points to.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Limited backlink index</h4>
              <p>Noticeably smaller than Ahrefs and Semrush. Missing links that competitors' tools surface. Professional link builders doing outreach will hit the ceiling fast and end up paying for a second tool.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Poor traffic estimation accuracy</h4>
              <p>Ranks lowest among major tools for traffic prediction accuracy (18.9% in independent testing). Use traffic estimates for relative comparisons only — don't quote them to clients as projections.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Site audit false positives</h4>
              <p>The audit flags issues that aren't actually problems. Every flagged item needs manual verification before you implement a fix. Adds overhead to the audit process that negates some of the time savings elsewhere.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>No local SEO toolkit whatsoever</h4>
              <p>No Google Business Profile management, no citation building, no review monitoring, no local pack tracking. Local businesses — dentists, plumbers, realtors, HVAC — need a completely different tool.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- STATS ROW -->
  <section>
    <div class="stats-row">
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">230<span class="accent">+</span></div><div class="stat-label">Regional Google databases</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">$69<span class="accent">/mo</span></div><div class="stat-label">Starting price · monthly</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">4.6<span class="accent">/5</span></div><div class="stat-label">G2 rating · 464 reviews</div></div>
      <div class="stat-cell"><div class="stat-num">9.4<span class="accent">/10</span></div><div class="stat-label">Support rating · G2</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- FEATURES IN DEPTH -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Features in depth</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Every major <span class="accent">Serpstat feature</span>, tested.</h2>
      <p>What's actually in the box — and what we found in hands-on testing.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Keyword research</h4>
              <p>Search volume with monthly trends and seasonality, keyword difficulty (0–100), CPC data, related keywords, questions, People Also Ask variations. Ten years of historical volume data. The Tree View hierarchical visualization and AI semantic clustering are the standout features in the category at this price.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Competitor analysis</h4>
              <p>Organic keywords with positions and traffic estimates, paid keywords and Google Ads data, traffic trends, visibility trends, market share analysis. Reliable for directional strategy — not precise enough for revenue projections. One of the stronger tools in the budget category for competitive intelligence.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Backlink analysis</h4>
              <p>Total backlinks and referring domains with trends, new/lost backlinks, anchor text distribution, domain authority scoring, toxic link identification, competitor comparison. Adequate for monitoring — materially smaller index than Ahrefs for deep link building research.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Site audit</h4>
              <p>Technical error detection with high/medium/low priority scoring, SDO Score for site health, Core Web Vitals, HTTPS checks, XML sitemap validation. JavaScript rendering on Team+ plans. Up to 1.5M pages on Agency plans. Watch for false positives — verify before implementing fixes.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Rank tracker</h4>
              <p>Desktop and mobile tracking, local rank tracking by city/region, competitor comparison, SERP feature tracking. Weekly updates standard, daily available. Ten years of historical position data. Reliable for trend monitoring — not as granular as SE Ranking for daily movements.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">06</span>
            <div>
              <h4>White-label reports and API</h4>
              <p>White-label reports on all plans (not gated to a premium tier). API access on all paid plans. Multi-user collaboration and project management built in. Good for agency workflows without paying extra for reporting features.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">07</span>
            <div>
              <h4>What's missing</h4>
              <p>Content writing, content optimization, publishing to CMS, Google Business Profile management, local citation tools, social media distribution. Serpstat is research — what happens after the research is entirely your team's work.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- PRICING -->
  <section class="cost-section">
    <div class="cost-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Pricing</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">What Serpstat <span class="accent">actually costs.</span></h2>
      <p>Four tiers with transparent monthly pricing. Annual billing saves 20%. 7-day free trial with no card required.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="cost-table">
      <div class="cost-row head">
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Tier</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Serpstat</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell">Key limits</div>
        <div class="cost-cell head-cell brand">theStacc equivalent</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Individual</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Solo SEO</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$69</div><div class="per">per month · $55 annual</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">1 user · 100 searches/day · 2,500 keywords</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">$49</div><div class="per">starter · content included</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
        <div class="cost-cell label"><div class="vert">Team</div><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">Small agency</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$129</div><div class="per">per month · $103 annual</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">3 users · 500 searches/day · 12,500 keywords</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">$99</div><div class="per">pro · 30 articles/mo</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-row">
