        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price">$299</div><div class="per">per month · $239 annual</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell"><div class="price" style="font-size:15px;font-weight:600;">6 users · 1,000 searches/day · 25,000 keywords</div></div>
        <div class="cost-cell brand"><div class="price brand">$199</div><div class="per">scale · 60 articles/mo</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-savings">
        <div class="big">Serpstat researches. theStacc publishes.</div>
        <div class="lbl">Serpstat tells you what to write. theStacc writes it, optimizes it, and publishes it — no writers required.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="cost-footnote">*All plans include keyword research, backlink analysis, site audit, rank tracker, competitor analysis, white-label reports, and API access. Annual billing saves ~20%. 7-day free trial, no card required.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
  <section class="problem-section">
    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">Who it's for</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">Who should buy Serpstat — <span class="accent">and who shouldn't.</span></h2>
      <p>The clearest filter we found after testing across freelance, agency, and in-house scenarios.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after">
        <div class="ba-head">
          <span class="ba-label">Buy Serpstat if</span>
          <h3 class="ba-title">You're a budget-conscious SEO researcher.</h3>
          <p class="ba-sub">Three signals Serpstat is the right fit.</p>
        </div>
        <ul class="ba-list">
